2/02/business/economy/chinese-companies-to-face-more-scrutiny-as-bill-clears-house.amp.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com.hk%2Famp%2Fs%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F12%2F02%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fchinese-companies-to-face-more-scrutiny-as-bill-clears-house.amp.html&d=u42ujRIT%2FE%2FeodHrCKN%2BOVpzQI%2FFghXCkDWT3grjsfs%3D&h=7eada102\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.google.com.hk/amp/s/www.nytimes.com/2020/12/02/business/economy/chinese-companies-to-face-more-scrutiny-as-bill-clears-house.amp.html</a>"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-03T01:52:24.000Z","msg":"WASHINGTON &mdash; The House of Representatives passed legislation on Wednesday that would increase oversight of Chinese companies listed on American stock markets, the latest attempt by the United States to scrutinize financial ties with China.<br />\n<br />\nThe bill, the Holding Foreign Companies Accountable Act, would require the companies to disclose more information about any ties to foreign governments and the Chinese Communist Party, and would remove them from the U.S. exchanges after three years if they did not provide U.S. regulators access to their audit information.<br />\n<br />\nThe Senate passed a companion bill in May, and President Trump is expected to sign it into law."},{"pid":"2c36f1ef0047110a7d6e242b32412286a0a8b2aa","tid":2309921,"uid":178875,"like":58,"dislike":0,"score":58,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-12-03T01:53:22.000Z","msg":"識玩<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n寫外國公司等於對全世界一視同仁無例外<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/yo.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n不過支國都會衝出黎吠<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/bark.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"904da6155ef213183b871db3fbd3d1170136dac9","tid":2309921,"uid":274996,"like":30,"dislike":1,"score":29,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-12-03T01:57:47.000Z","msg":"法案通過當然好，但要睇政府行政既執行鬆緊，呢樣睇總統"},{"pid":"3a7ad91b5c0cd16631358e26cb91421acdd0722d","tid":2309921,"uid":8873,